title: which provided de-identified excess tissue to the laboratory immediately following surgical resection. Specimens used for cell culture were dissociated with a Papain dissociation kit (Worthington). Cells were cultured adherently in media containing 50% Neurobasal medium (Gibco) and 50% Dulbecco's modified Eagle medium (DMEM) with B27 (without vitamin A
column11: and 5% FBS. All cultured cells were used within five passages of dissociation.
